nhc_headline: ...OCTAVE STILL A TROPICAL STORM BUT LIKELY TO DISSIPATE ON THURSDAY...
summary: ...OCTAVE STILL A TROPICAL STORM BUT LIKELY TO DISSIPATE ON THURSDAY... As of 8:00 AM PDT Wed Oct 08 the center of Octave was located near 15.4, -116.2 with movement E at 12 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1003 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 40 mph.
